  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Long term results after pulmonary vein isolation (PVI) with robotic navigation in patients
      with drug refractory atrial fibrillation are not inferior to manual radiofrequency current
      ablation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
